<HEADLINE>
FT  24 SEP 94 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Black pepper prices increased very sharply in the past fortnight, reports
Man Producten. The improving demand for black pepper from consuming markets,
which had been inactive for many months, pushed prices up in all origins.
Suppliers there have almost all withdrawn and apparently prefer to watch
further developments. Black pepper faq traded at about USDollars 2,300 a
tonne on the European spot market and in the US asta was at Dollars 1.20 a
poundl. Whites prices only climbed moderately. Spot white was at Dollars
3,200 a tonne and September/October shipment at Dollars 3,150, cif, in
limited quantities. Only sporadic buying took place.
</TEXT>
