The company said that while first time buyers had fallen away, sales of its
top of the range properties were increasing. Once conditions improved, its
low cost land bank would enable it to 'maximise profit contribution'.
Earnings per share were 3.53p (2.26p) and the interim dividend is unchanged
at 1.75p.
