<HEADLINE>
FT  23 SEP 94 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Prices at the Australian wool sales have declined for the first time this
season. At Sydney and Adelaide earlier this week it became clear that the
market had at last turned. The Eastern market indicator actually fell by 11
cents on Wednesday, marking a change of direction which is generally
welcomed after the long rise in merino prices. A breathing-space would
certainly be appreciated, although it is recognised that the strength in the
international wool markets is still firmly based, and could reveal itself in
higher prices again before long. One important factor in such a development
would be a renewal of Chinese buying in volume when a lower price-level is
established.
</TEXT>
