<HEADLINE>
FT  23 SEP 94 / Technology (Worth Watching): Computer aid in drug screening
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By VANESSA HOULDER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Researchers working in the fast-growing field of combinatorial chemistry aim
to make a wide variety of compounds simultaneously, which are then screened
to find useful characteristics.
The first set of computer tools to assist in this process have been devised
by Tripos, a US scientific software company. Tripos's Mass Screen software
will assist researchers to generate vast 'libraries' of compounds and
manipulate the data as they search for new leads in drug development.
Tripos: US, tel 314 647 1099; fax 314 647 9241
</TEXT>
